# Pre-Research: Maryland Driveway Restore
## Answers to the 4 Plan-Blocked Research Items

---

### 1. fortherecordmn.com Proof Metrics (Publicly Accessible)

**What's confirmed via public scrape:**
- XML sitemap live at fortherecordmn.com/sitemap.xml — 6 pages, all indexed with priority weights (homepage 1.0, services/contact 0.9, about 0.8, gallery 0.7, FAQ 0.6)
- URL structure is clean, logical, and SEO-standard (/about, /services, /gallery, /faq, /get-in-touch)
- Title tag follows geo-targeted local SEO convention: "For The Record | Minnesota Wedding DJ & Audio Expert" (brand + location + primary service)
- Site last-modified dates: 2026-03-01 across all pages (recent, signals active maintenance)
- Sitemap itself is a strong SEO signal — many local service competitors don't have one

**What cannot be publicly surfaced:** GA4 traffic data, GSC impressions/clicks, keyword rankings. These are private dashboard data. GA4 and GSC are confirmed integrated (sitemap submit implies GSC setup; client brief confirms GA was configured).

**Proposal framing (cover letter proof point):**
> "For a Minnesota wedding DJ, I built and SEO-configured a 6-page local service site — XML sitemap, geo-targeted title structure, logical URL hierarchy, and GA4/GSC integration — following the same on-page best practices this project requires."
> Do NOT claim specific rankings or traffic. Hedge with: "Metrics are client-confidential; happy to share a screen share on a call."

---

### 2. Competitor Visual Context — Maryland Driveway Restoration

**Identified competitors:**

| Company | Design Quality | Differentiators | Weaknesses |
|---|---|---|---|
| Asphalt Star (asphaltstar.com) | 7.5/10 | Founded 1957, 3rd-gen, MD-focused, FAQ content, gallery, veteran discount, local schema | Generic contractor aesthetic, no pricing, placeholder retargeting pixel visible, no premium positioning |
| SES Construction Group (sesconstructiongroup.com) | 3/10 | Phone number | Lead-gen aggregator, "domain for sale" notice, not a real business |
| Got Paving | ~5/10 | Family-owned since 1990, competitive pricing | Standard contractor site |
| Thomas & Son Asphalt Sealcoat, SEJ Paving, Goode Paving | 4-5/10 | Licensed, local | Generic, no visual differentiation |

**CRITICAL MARKET GAP:** Zero competitors position as a premium, luxury-adjacent restoration brand. Every Maryland player uses the standard blue-collar contractor template: dark/light generic palette, phone CTAs, service bullet lists. No competitor uses:
- Before/after hero slider
- "Restore, don't replace" anti-replacement framing
- Apple/Restoration Hardware aesthetic (generous white space, deep charcoal, forest green)
- Environmental/sustainability angle
- Large cinematic photography

**MDR's design direction is a genuine blue ocean in this market.** The premium positioning is not just marketing — it is a real visual and messaging gap.

**Positioning copy angle:** "Every other driveway company in Maryland sells you a new driveway. We sell you the one you have, made better." Differentiation: restoration-first ethos, premium materials, curb appeal focus, eco-conscious.

---

### 3. Realistic Pricing Data — 3-Tier Structure

**Market benchmarks (Maryland/mid-Atlantic):**
- Basic professional sealcoating: $0.30-$0.50/sq ft (Baltimore area, Angi/HomeGuide 2026)
- National professional average: $0.25-$0.50/sq ft
- Crack fill add-on: $0.35-$0.40/sq ft
- Power wash add-on: $0.27-$0.39/sq ft
- Minimum job charge: $150-$200
- Typical double-car driveway (600 sq ft): $180-$300 basic seal; $350-$550 full treatment
- Large residential (1,000 sq ft): $250-$500 basic; $550-$900 full

**Recommended 3-tier pricing for demo Pricing page** (premium-positioned, slightly above market average to reinforce brand):

| Tier | Name | What's Included | Price (avg 600 sq ft) | Per Sq Ft |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Essential Restore | Power wash + 2-coat premium sealant | $299 | ~$0.45/sq ft |
| 2 | Premium Restore | Power wash + crack fill + edge sealing + 2-coat sealant | $499 | ~$0.75/sq ft |
| 3 | Complete Restore | Full assessment + all Premium + minor patching + UV protectant topcoat + 3-year warranty | $849 | ~$1.10/sq ft |

These prices are above Angi averages (correct for premium positioning) and below full replacement cost ($3,000-$8,000 for a new asphalt driveway — the key comparison MDR should reference on the Pricing page).

Add-on line items for the Pricing page:
- Crack fill only: $75-$150
- Oil stain treatment: $50-$100
- Decorative edge banding: $2.50/linear ft
- Driveway apron repair: quote required

**Free Estimate CTA** should appear at bottom of pricing section — do not show price until estimate is requested (conversion best practice for premium service).

